Global Funds Buy Net 3.52 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-04-04T03:25:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/global-funds-buy-net-3-52-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 3.52
billion rupees ($79 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
April 1, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 5.3 percent to 834.4 billion rupees, or 37.9
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 4.15 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on April 1, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
